00:06:41.400 --> 00:06:43.620
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:46.200
Be careful of these common traps.

00:06:46.530 --> 00:06:51.510
Many people confuse a hub which
broadcasts to all with a switch, which

00:06:51.510 --> 00:06:53.880
smartly sends to a specific destination.

00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:57.330
Also, don't mix up a router and a switch.

00:06:57.690 --> 00:07:00.420
Routers connect different
networks while switches.

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:02.520
Connect devices within the same network.

00:07:02.990 --> 00:07:05.780
People also underestimate
the geographic scope.

00:07:06.110 --> 00:07:07.340
LAN is local.

00:07:07.490 --> 00:07:08.690
WAN is wide.

00:07:09.170 --> 00:07:10.909
A classic mistake is forgetting.

00:07:10.909 --> 00:07:15.560
The S in H-T-T-P-S stands for
secure meaning encryption.

00:07:15.980 --> 00:07:19.010
Another is mixing up
protocols for sending email.

00:07:19.170 --> 00:07:25.470
Which is SMTP with protocols for receiving
it like POP three and imap, and please

00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:27.900
learn the OSI layer order correctly.

00:07:28.230 --> 00:07:33.840
Lastly, understand that an IP address is
logical and can change, but a MAC address

00:07:33.840 --> 00:07:35.940
is physical and fixed to the device.

